  <title>AFL round 20: Angus Monfries to play first senior game in two years</title>
  <content>
Angus Monfries is poised to play his first senior game in close to two years after being named in Port Adelaide's 22 on Friday for Sunday's showdown against Adelaide.
The former Bomber last played at AFL level in round 22, 2015, having been suspended for the 2016 season, one of 34 past and present Dons banned for doping infractions.Photo: Pat Scala
Monfries is the last of the AFL-listed banned Bombers to return. He and Aidyn Johnson replace Matthew Broadbent (ankle) and Matt White.
The Crows confirmed the inclusion of Eddie Betts, Jake Lever and Brad Crouch, with swingman Andy Otten among three omissions.

Richmond will welcome back Dion Prestia for Sunday's clash with Hawthorn after a week out with knee soreness. He replaces Shai Bolton, while Jack Riewoldt (eye surgery) will miss another week.
The Hawks have recalled youngster Teia Miles in place of suspended veteran Luke Hodge.
St Kilda have brought in Nick Riewoldt and Koby Stevens for Sunday's clash with West Coast. Matthew Priddis was named as an emergency for the Eagles.
Daniel Cherny and AAP
